            "type": "text",
            "text": "Capabilities and Model Specifications"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Nanonets OCR S excels in extracting structured text from images and PDFs, with support for over 100 languages and common document formats like JPEG, PNG, and TIFF. It leverages a transformer-based architecture optimized for OCR, reducing hallucinations and improving field-level accuracy on tabular data. In contrast, OpenAI's models, such as GPT-4 with vision, are general-purpose and may require more prompting to achieve similar precision, which can increase token usage and latency."
          }
        ]
      },
