      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "No model is perfect, and Nanonets OCR S has limitations. It performs best on printed text and may struggle with highly stylized fonts or low-quality images. OpenAI's models can handle more diverse inputs but at the cost of consistency. Common issues with Nanonets include API timeouts during high load and lower accuracy on handwritten text."
          }
